t 4 AC in dodge bonuses.  Certain spells like armor add both AC and dodge AC.  <br>
Now how does dodge AC stack with normal dexterity AC?  If you wear studded leather you get 5 max dex AC (yes it says 4 AC but it's actually 5)--so would your dexterity AC put you at the cap, eating up most of your dodge AC bonus?  <br>
<br>
Ok, to explain:  18 dex= 4 AC dex<br>
mobility + evasion= 4 AC in dodge.<br>
<br>
Dex AC of studded =5 AC<br>
So would you get 8 effective AC from dodge and dexterity, or 5 AC?<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A> at: 8/5/02 12:08:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ullabaktharr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llabak Tharr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/5/02 12:12:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does AC dodge work?</span><hr size=1> Wuf, that's a heck of a question.<br>
