<center>Can ya dig it?</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/5/02 12:15:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does AC dodge work?</span><hr size=1> Yeah, the thing is that dodge AC doesn't show up on your character sheet.  I'm guessing that your dodge AC is capped at the armor's Dex AC limit, so if you wear say, a breastplate your mobility is going to waste... if it's not a separate cap from dex AC, then you need to wear padded armor to take advantage of it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ullabaktharr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llabak Tharr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/5/02 12:34:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does AC dodge work?</span><hr size=1> Are you sure about that?  I could swear that my monk's boots were +dodge and they showed up on the sheet.<br>
<br>
Maybe that's just cause he was a monk though :/ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaneurtreewalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aneur Treewalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/02 3:16:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does AC dodge work?</span><hr size=1> AC gained from feats like Dodge and Mobility dont show up of the character sheet because the bonuses only kick in in certain situation<br>
<br>
Armor that gives a dodge bonus (ie boots of striding) will show up on the character sheet<br>
