<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: Please read our sig/personal pic rules. Both mustn't be more than 15kbyte combined. - ShadowCross</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 8/6/02 11:59:22 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/02 10:47:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does AC dodge work?</span><hr size=1> Wha--?  <br>
So you have to have a lot of money to use your dodge?  Because normal armor doesn't seem to have a dodge AC.  <br>
I was looking back at some of my combat and it seems that in one-on-one combat my dodge may be in effect (rolls of 19 missed me), but if I'm under attack by multiple enemies, my dodge bonus is gone (rolls of 15 hit me).  Could this be how it works?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ullabaktharr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llabak Tharr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/02 11:25:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does AC dodge work?</span><hr size=1> From the PHB, page 119:<br>
<br>
Dodge bonuses:  Some other AC bonuses represent actively avoiding blows, such as the dwarf's AC bonus against giants or the AC bonus for fighting defensively.  These bonuses are called dodge bonuses.  Any situation that denies you our Dexterity bonus also denies you dodge bonuses <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (Wearing armor, however, does not limit these bonuses the way it limits a dexterity bonus to AC).</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Dodge Feat:  Improves your AC by +1 against <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> a single opponent</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Dexterity Modifier: ...Sometimes you can't use your Dexterity bonus (if you ahve one).  The AC bonus you get for a high Dexterity represents your ability to dodge incoming attacks.  If you can't reat to a blow, you can't use your Dexterity bonus on AC.  You lose your Dexterity bonus when, for example, and invisibe opponent attacs you, you're hanging on for dear life to the face of a crumbling cliff high above a river of lava, or you're caught flat-footed at the beginning of a combat.<br>
<br>
Bold type added <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/02 11:30:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does AC dodge work?</span><hr size=1> Hmmm... it's not often you fight one opponent of course.  It's good to have at least one level of rogue (or barbarian) so you never get caught flat footed and lose your dex bonus or your dodge bonus.  I'm not sure under what situations you can get caught flatfooted though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukintire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kintire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/7/02 8:34:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does AC dodge work?</span><hr size=1> You are flatfooted in combat until your first action. That is, during the surprise round (if any) and any actions at a higher initiative than you during the first round.<br>
<br>
And the bonus from the dodge feat works fine when you are fighting multiple opponents; just only against one of them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/7/02 12:06:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does AC dodge work?</span><hr size=1> Your dodge bonus works against whatever creature you're currently attacking (it'll have tiny red arrows flashing underneath it).<br>
<br>
You can check this by watching the combat chatter in your chat bar.  The monster you have targeted will be taking swings against 1 higher AC.<br>
<br>
